{
  "doc_id": "9959",
  "text": "Among the different types of vegetation that exist in the Atlantic Forest, the ancient grassy fields, known as \"Campos de Altitude\", form a forest-grassland mosaic in the southern portion of this biome, and are one of the less studied and most threatened vegetation in Brazil [CITATION_1] . Relative to the species from forests, species from grassy ecosystems are poorly studied and conserved [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Furthermore, it is predicted that the medicinal species of these regions and ecosystems are highly vulnerable. Two factors have led to this situation: the lack of study of these species and the increased worldwide demand for medicinal plants resulting in direct removal of these species from their natural habitat [CITATION_4] . The vulnerability of these species increases because often, the most commonly used medicinal plant species in certain regions of the world are unknown to genetic conservation researchers and therefore, are not considered for conservation.",
